$$7x + 8y + 9z - (\gamma  - 1) = A(4x + 5y + 6z - \beta ) + B(x + 2y + 3z - \alpha )$$<br/><br/>On equating the coefficients,<br/><br/>4A + B = 7 .... (i)<br/><br/>5A + 2B = 8 .... (ii)<br/><br/>and $$-$$ ($$\gamma$$ $$-$$ 1) = $$-$$ A$$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\alpha$$B ..... (iii)<br/><br/>On solving Eqs. (i) and (ii), we get A = 2 and B = $$-$$1<br/><br/>From Eq. (iii), we get<br/><br/>$$-$$ $$\gamma$$ + 1 = $$-$$ 2$$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\alpha$$($$-$$1)<br/><br/>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\alpha$$ $$-$$ 2$$\beta$$ + $$\gamma$$ = 1 ..... (iv)<br/><br/>Now, determinant of<br/><br/>$$M = \left| M \right| = \left| {\matrix{
