 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 & 0 & 0  \cr 
   0 & 1 & 0  \cr 
   0 & 0 & 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br/><br/>Hence, option (a) is correct.<br/><br/>For option (b)<br/><br/>$$\left| {EQ + PF{Q^{ - 1}}} \right| = \left| {EQ} \right| + \left| {PF{Q^{ - 1}}} \right|$$ .... (i)<br/><br/>$$\because$$ | E | = 0 and | F | = 0 and | Q | $$\ne$$ 0<br/><br/>$$\therefore$$ $$\left| {EQ} \right| = \left| E \right|\left| Q \right| = 0$$<br/><br/>and $$\left| {PF{Q^{ - 1}}} \right| = {{\left| P \right|\left| F \right|} \over {\left| Q \right|}} = 0$$<br/><br/>Let $$R = EQ + PF{Q^{ - 1}}$$ .... (ii)<br/><br/>$$ \Rightarrow RQ = E{Q^2} + PF = E{Q^2} + {P^2}EP = E{Q^2} + EP$$ [$$\because$$ P<sup>2</sup> = I]<br/><br/>$$ = E({Q^2} + P)$$<br/><br/>$$ \Rightarrow \left| {RQ} \right| = \left| {E({Q^2} + P)} \right|$$<br/><br/>$$ \Rightarrow \left| R \right|\left| Q \right| = \left| E \right|\left| {{Q^2} + P} \right| = 0$$ [$$\because$$ | E | = O]<br/><br/>$$ \Rightarrow \left| R \right| = 0$$ (as $$\left| Q \right| \ne 0$$) ..... (iii)<br/><br/>From Eqs. (ii) and (iii), we get Eq. (i) is true.<br/><br/>Hence, option (b) is correct.<br/><br/>For option (c)<br/><br/>$$\left| {{{(EF)}^3}} \right| > {\left| {EF} \right|^2}$$<br/><br/>i.e. 0 > 0 which is false.<br/><br/>For option (d)<br/><br/>$$\because$$ $${P^2} = I \Rightarrow {P^{ - 1}} = P$$<br/><br/>$$\therefore$$ $${P^{ - 1}}FP = PFP = PPEPP = E$$<br/><br/>So, $$E + {P^{ - 1}}FP = E + E = 2E$$<br/><br/>$$ \Rightarrow Tr(E + {P^{ - 1}}FP) = Tr(2E) = 2Tr(E)$$ ..... (iv)<br/><br/>and $${P^{ - 1}}EP + F$$<br/><br/>$$ \Rightarrow PEP + F = 2PEP$$ [$$\because$$ F = PEP]<br/><br/>$$\therefore$$ $$Tr(2PEP) = 2Tr(PEP) = 2Tr(F) = 2Tr(E)$$ ..... (v)<br/><br/>From Eqs. (iv) and (v) option (d) is also correct.
